### 1. Slider

**Purpose:** User drags a thumb to express a sentiment on a 5-point scale.

**Layout (right panel):**
```
eyebrow:   "Drag the slider"   (Alata 13px green)
title:     Question text        (ABeeZee 26px)
tooltip:   floating above thumb (green pill, Alata 14px 600 white)
track:     full width, height 64px, border-radius 20px, bg rgba(0,0,0,0.06)
  - 5 dots evenly distributed (10×10px circles, rgba(0,0,0,0.12))
  - active dot: rgba(0,169,80,0.5)
  - thumb: 52×48px, border-radius 16px, background #00A950,
           box-shadow 0 4px 20px rgba(0,169,80,0.35)
           contains 3 vertical lines (2px × 20px, rgba(255,255,255,0.7))
labels:    "Very scared" — "I feel fine!" — "Amazing!" (ABeeZee 11px, rgba(0,0,0,0.35))
```

**Tooltip:**
```
background: #00A950, border-radius:10px, padding:6px 14px
arrow: CSS border-trick pointing downward, color #00A950
text: Alata 13px 600 white
positions/labels: [8%, "Very scared."], [25%, "A bit scared."],
                  [43%, "I feel fine!"], [61%, "Pretty good!"], [80%, "Amazing!"]
```

**Behavior:**
- Draggable on mouse + touch
- Snaps to nearest of 5 positions on release
- Tooltip and thumb animate together (`transition: left 0.18s cubic-bezier(.4,0,.2,1)`)
- Active dot updates on each position change

